defaultWritten evidence from Chartered Institution of Highways and Transportation (CIHT) (CYS 057)
default&#xa0;
defaultCIHT is a membership organisation representing over 12,000 people who work in the highways and transportation sector.  CIHT membe
defaultrs plan, design, build, operate and maintain best-in-class transport systems and infrastructure, whilst respecting the imperatives of improving safety, ensuring economic competitiveness and minimising environmental impact.
default&#xa0;
defaultCIHT welcomes the opportunity to
default submit evidence to the Committee’s call for evidence on 
defaultCycling Safety
default. CIHT responses are based on inputs from members of our 
defaultRoad Safety and Urban Design
default panel
