defaultCycling has substantial health benefits for physical and mental wellbeing, as well as having a 
defaultmuch lower
default 
defaultenvironmental impact than motor transport, and CIHT continues to urge all highway authorities to maintain these bene
defaultfits while delivering infrastructure and other actions to 
defaultreduce
default cyclist injury
default. Although there 
defaulthas been a decline in the level of risk to cycling over the longer term, there have been more recent increases in the rate of killed and serious injuries
default, which
default is at odds with other transport modes
default.
