default2.0default              defaultWhat Central and local Government could do to improve cycldefaulting defaultsdefaultafety?default&#xa0;
default2.1default              
defaultSuccessive Governments have demonstrated a commitment to promoting cycling by 
defaultdedicated 
defaultfunding, issuing policy not
defaultes and publishing guidance.  
defaultUnfortunately t
defaulthe outcome has been mixed, with some provision being disjointed or of limited use to 
defaultmore confident 
defaultcyclists.  However
default the recent increases in the levels of cycling in some places, particularly in London and the 
defaultcentres of the larger cities, as well as the ‘Cycling Demonstration Towns’, indicates that
default promoting cycling is succeeding.  Success in terms of safety 
defaultmust now follow and will 
defaultcome from joint working 
defaultbetween central and local government
default, the Institutions 
defaultand cycling organisations
default, 
defaultidentifying the challenges
default and developing 
defaultand implementing 
defaultbetter solutions
default.
default&#xa0;
default2.2default              
defaultIn order to make this happen, s
defaultenior political and executive commitment at both national and local level 
defaultmust 
defaultbe
default achieved
default to 
defaultsupport 
